HEADWORD: Cui bono
<hw>Cui` bo"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L.]</ety> <def>Lit., for
whose benefit; incorrectly understood, it came to be used in the sense,
of what good or use; and hence, (what) purpose; object; specif., the
ultimate object of life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cuinage</ent>⟦br⟧
